{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We-- like I said, we didn't-- I think on my whole stay in Bergen-Belsen, I took two showers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And to take a shower was a-- was a big thing because they had to take us out of the camp to someone else to take a shower.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That's why, they-- I guess they never wanted to bother in the first place because in our part of the camp, there were no showers.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Anyway, so like I said, things got worse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had this-- continued to have this roll call.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "In the meanwhile, next to us were people from other camps who had walked into the-- brought into the Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And if they didn't have typhus, they had typhus by the time they got there from us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "They got it from us, probably.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And they were undernourished.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I mean, we were also, of course, undernourished tremendously, but they were even worse.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So they died.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "You know, like, you know, you could see the bodies lying all over the-- all over the camp and piled up in front of the barracks, you know, right to the way roof.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And pits, they dug pits because the crematorium didn't function.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] Like I told you before, the crematorium burned down.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It was not a good thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You know, people might say, oh, that's good.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It's not good because you couldn't burn the bodies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we did notice at one time in October, November next door to us there were some people speaking Dutch who had come-- well, we didn't know where they came from.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They had come from Auschwitz, apparently, who were actually Dutch who had survived Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "They all-- they were women, actually, who had gotten to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "You know, of course, I didn't know at the time, I didn't know it. was-- you know, Anne Frank was amongst those who-- who were in that part of the camp.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And for a while, they were next door to us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And I remember you-- you couldn't see anybody because it was a barbed wire with straw in between.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But you could talk to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And I thought maybe a cousin would be there or something.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "So I went there to-- to look, but I didn't find anybody.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Other people did find some-- some relatives there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And conditions in a way became untenable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "You know, it's hard to describe so many years later, you know.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I don't know how we even survived those few months because if you were lucky, you had this one slice of bread a week.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "You had this turnip soup.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And then what we did get, I think, which may have helped, we got-- got-- once we got Red Cross parcels.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "In October of 1944, we got parcels from the Red Cross, which had been sent I don't know from where.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And they distributed to everybody a parcel, which was some-- a few dry goods.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And by the way, afterwards they found not far from Bergen-Belson a huge storage house full of those parcels which were just put there and never bought to us, you know.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "So this continued for those-- all those months.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And really, the Germans themselves were almost afraid to come into the camp because of the disease.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The kapos were there, of course, and they themself made the roll call in the morning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And I remember many times it was snowing, and it was cold, and they made us stand.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "And some of the kapos, when you knew them, they would have turned the other way.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And I would run away and hide in one of the barracks because I didn't want to stand outside in the cold.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And this helped me to survive, I guess.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "The counting didn't mean anything anyway because people were dying by so many that I think it was just a sham, the whole thing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "We-- this continued and-- and-- for-- for December, January, February, March.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "I-- I-- this-- it's like-- in a way like a blur.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "I can't tell you, really, what I did day by day.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "I think day by day, it really was a struggle just to live. | Know that-- that I used to try to scrounge food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "One of the things, for instance, which I did at one time was outside the barbed wire in another-- you know, across the camp-- it was part of the camp.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "It was a kitchen which was used-- I don't know whether it was used for-- for the Germans or for some privileged prisoners, but there was food there.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And at night-- and there was-- at the beginning, some Jews from our camp were working there, and they used to bring food with them for their families.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
